#########################################
#  Solution

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR 
The graphs of both \( f(x) = e^x \ \) and \( \ f(x) = e^{-x} \ \) have the same horizontal asymptote. Their asymptote is the $BITALIC x${EITALIC}-axis, whose equation is \( y=0 \). The graph of \( y=\ln{x} \) is asymptotic to the $BITALIC y${EITALIC}-axis, hence the equation of its asymptote is \( x=0 \).
$BR
END_SOLUTION

      

